&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The type of radiation used to get relief from body aches is infrared radiation (IR). &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, option 1 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrared Radiation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Infrared therapy is commonly used in physiotherapy and medical treatments to relieve body aches and muscle pain.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Infrared radiation penetrates the skin and generates heat, improving blood circulation, relaxing muscles, and reducing stiffness.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Infrared lamps and heating pads are widely used for pain relief in conditions like arthritis, muscle sprains, and joint discomfort.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is also beneficial for reducing inflammation and accelerating the healing process.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This non-invasive treatment is effective for localized pain and muscle relaxation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Out of the 22 amino acids required for protein synthesis, &lt;strong&gt;9 are considered essential amino acids&lt;/strong&gt; for humans because the body cannot synthesize them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These 9 essential amino acids must be obtained through the diet as they play a critical role in various physiological processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 9 essential amino acids are: &lt;strong&gt;histidine, isoleucine, leucine, lysine, methionine, phenylalanine, threonine, tryptophan, and valine&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These amino acids are found abundantly in foods like &lt;strong&gt;meat, fish, eggs, dairy products, soy, and quinoa&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The remaining 13 amino acids are classified as non-essential because the body can synthesize them from other compounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amino Acids:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Amino acids are organic compounds that combine to form proteins, which are vital for the structure and function of cells.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They consist of an amino group, a carboxyl group, and a side chain that varies between different amino acids.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential vs Non-Essential Amino Acids:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential amino acids&lt;/strong&gt; cannot be synthesized by the body and must be obtained through diet.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-essential amino acids&lt;/strong&gt; can be produced by the body, even if they are not present in the diet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conditionally Essential Amino Acids:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Some amino acids, such as arginine, cysteine, and glutamine, are considered conditionally essential.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Under certain conditions like illness or stress, the body may not produce enough of these amino acids, making dietary intake necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Protein Sources:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Animal-based foods (e.g., meat, fish, eggs, and dairy) are considered complete proteins as they provide all 9 essential amino acids.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Plant-based foods (e.g., beans, lentils, and nuts) can be combined to form complete protein profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role of Amino Acids:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Amino acids are critical for processes like enzyme production, tissue repair, and nutrient absorption.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They also play roles in hormone synthesis, immune function, and energy production.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thermosetting plastics, such as melamine-formaldehyde resin, are used in making floor tiles. &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, option 4 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These materials harden irreversibly when heated, making them durable, heat-resistant, and scratch-proof, which are ideal properties for floor tiles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Melamine, combined with formaldehyde, forms a strong and rigid plastic, extensively used in construction and decorative applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
